properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 8 at 4:12AM PST until January 9 at 1:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...Flood Warnings continues for the following rivers in
Washington...

Snohomish River At Snohomish affecting Snohomish County
Snoqualmie River Near Carnation affecting King County

No hydrologically significant precipitation in the forecast for the
next two days. Another front will arrive on Friday but snow levels
will be low, below 2000 feet, keeping the precipitation in the
form of snow in the mountains limiting runoff into the rivers.

The Flood Warning continues for
The Snoqualmie River Near Carnation
* Until late tonight.
* At  4:00 AM Wednesday the stage was 55.7 feet.
* Flood stage is 54.0 feet.
* Minor flooding is occurring and Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river crested at 56.3 feet at 9 PM Tuesday and will
continue to fall to below flood stage this afternoon.
* Impact...At 54.0 feet, the Snoqualmie River will flood much of the
farm land and several roads from Fall City downstream through
Carnation and Duvall.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.

NWSheadline: Flood Warning extended until late tonight
